g.text: *The computer, main monitor, keyboard and mice are obviously needed if you plan to stream games!

text.tspan: a second monitor or a laptop makes it
easier for you to see the alerts and the chat
while playing your games. It really does not
need to be expansive.
A confortable chair is very important for a
streamer. It will be a game changer in the
long term, especially if you do long streams.
You definitively need a microphone.
The shockmount, boom arm and pop filter
are not necessairy but highly recommanded
since they prevent undesired noises.
*The price for a microphone is around 70-150$, and the
shockmount and boom arm from 35$ to 200$.
A webcam is generally appeciated by the
viewers. It is always nice to see live reactions
from the streamer!
Good and confortable headphones will
increase your personnal experience.
Take closed headphones because open ones
can shoot sound around and it can mess with
the microphone.
Click on a component to
get the description
Go over this box to see all
avaliable components

text.tspan: So you want to start a streaming channel? Awesome!
